.TH PEERCOIND "1" "June 2018" "peercoind 0.6.4"
.SH NAME
peercoind \- peer-to-peer network based digital currency
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
peercoind [options]
peercoind [options] <command> [params] - Send command to peercoind
peercoind [options] help - List commands
peercoind [options] help <command> - Get help for a command
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
This  manual page documents the peercoind program. Peercoin is a peer-to-peer digital currency. Peer-to-peer (P2P) means that there is no central authority to issue new money or keep track of transactions. Instead, these tasks are managed collectively by the nodes of the network. Advantages:

Peercoins can be sent easily through the Internet, without having to trust middlemen. Transactions are designed to be irreversible. Be safe from instability caused by fractional reserve banking and central banks. The limited inflation of the Peercoin systemâ€™s money supply is distributed evenly (by held coins) throughout the network, not monopolized by banks.

.SH OPTIONS
